The paper discusses large-scale propagation path loss models for use in fifth-generation wireless systems, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The models are specifically designed for use in microwave and millimeter-wave (mmWave) radio spectrum, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of these models in urban macrocell, urban microcell, and indoor office and shopping mall scenarios, which are related to mobile computing (cs.MA) and systems and control (cs.SY).
